<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-04-02</DATELINE><TITLE>Annotation: The COVID-19 pandemic and clinical orthopaedic and trauma surgery</TITLE><BODY>Abstract This article provides a brief overview of the current COVID-19 pandemic crisis and the impact on trauma and orthopaedic surgeons. The principles of protect, avoid, restrict and abbreviate are recommended. Coordination of response, communication and support are also important. The versatility of orthopaedic surgeons lends them to having an important role.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>